RawSSG - Raw Static Site Generator
===================================

RawSSG is a minimalist static site generator built with Rust.
Keep your content raw, simple, and fast.

INSTALLATION
------------

1. Install Rust:
   curl --proto '=https' --tlsv1.2 -sSf https://sh.rustup.rs | sh

2. Clone and build:
   git clone https://github.com/neuxdotdev/rawssg.git
   cd rawssg
   cargo build --release

3. Install globally (optional):
   cargo install --path .

QUICK START
-----------

# Create a new site
rawssg init my-site
cd my-site

# Build the site
rawssg build

# Start development server
rawssg serve

# Watch for changes
rawssg build --watch

BASIC USAGE
-----------

Initialize a new project:
  rawssg init [path]

Build your site:
  rawssg build [--watch] [--minify] [--clean]

Start development server:
  rawssg serve [--port 8080] [--watch]

Create new content:
  rawssg new post "My Post Title"
  rawssg new page "About" --draft

Clean build output:
  rawssg clean

Validate configuration:
  rawssg validate

PROJECT STRUCTURE
-----------------

my-site/
├── .rawfile          # Configuration file
├── content/          # Your .rw and .md files
│   ├── index.rw
│   ├── about.rw
│   └── posts/
├── templates/        # Handlebars templates
│   ├── base.html
│   ├── _sidebar.html
│   ├── _content.html
│   └── _footer.html
├── dist/             # Built site (auto-generated)
└── build-info.json   # Build metadata

.RW FILE FORMAT
---------------

Example with frontmatter:
---
title: Home Page
slug: index
date: 2026-01-01
draft: false
tags: [home, welcome]
---
Your raw content here.
URLs auto-link: https://github.com/neuxdotdev
Email: neuxdev1@gmail.com

Plain text example:
Just write content.
Links work: https://example.com
Email: hello@example.com

CONFIGURATION (.rawfile)
------------------------

{
  "version": "0.1.0",
  "title": "My Site",
  "description": "Site description",
  "favicon": "favicon.ico",
  "base_url": "https://example.com",
  "content": {
    "format": "plain",
    "extensions": ["rw", "md"],
    "ignore": ["drafts/"],
    "drafts": false
  },
  "build": {
    "output_dir": "dist",
    "clean_build": false,
    "minify": { "html": false, "css": false, "js": false },
    "generate": { "sitemap": true, "robots": true, "feed": true },
    "strict": false
  },
  "template": {
    "dir": "templates",
    "default_layout": "base.html",
    "partials": ["sidebar", "footer"]
  },
  "nav": [
    { "title": "Home", "url": "/" },
    { "title": "About", "url": "/about" }
  ],
  "footer": {
    "text": "Built with RawSSG",
    "links": [{ "title": "GitHub", "url": "https://github.com/neuxdotdev" }],
    "copyright": "© 2026 Your Name"
  }
}

FEATURES
--------

* Raw text content (.rw files)
* Frontmatter support (YAML)
* Handlebars templating
* Auto-link detection (URLs, emails)
* Dark/light theme switching
* Mobile-responsive sidebar
* Live reload with --watch
* Sitemap, robots.txt, RSS feed
* HTML/CSS/JS minification
* Draft content support
* Multiple content formats (.rw, .md)

TEMPLATES
---------

RawSSG uses Handlebars templates with these built-in helpers:

{{eq a b}}      - Check if a equals b
{{neq a b}}     - Check if a not equals b
{{lowercase s}} - Convert to lowercase
{{date d}}      - Format date (YYYY-MM-DD → Month Day, Year)

Available partials by default:
{{> sidebar }}  - Navigation sidebar
{{> content }}  - Page content
{{> footer }}   - Site footer

DEPLOYMENT
----------

1. Build for production:
   rawssg build --minify

2. Deploy to any static hosting:
   Netlify:    netlify deploy --dir=dist
   Vercel:     vercel --prod
   GitHub Pages: deploy dist/ folder
   Cloudflare Pages: connect repository

TROUBLESHOOTING
---------------

Error: "No content files found"
  Create content/index.rw: mkdir -p content && echo "Hello" > content/index.rw

Error: "Config not found"
  Run: rawssg init .

Error: "Template not found"
  Run: rawssg build (auto-creates default templates)

Server won't start:
  Install Python 3 or PHP, or use: rawssg serve --port 3000

